Ext.data.JsonP['Workbench_Actions']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Workbench Actions</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-31524866\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Workbench Actions</h1>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-31524866_WorkbenchActions-Actions\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Actions</span></h2>\n    <p>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Workbench_Actions-section-src-31524866_WorkbenchActions-Requirements\">Requirements</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Workbench_Actions-section-src-31524866_WorkbenchActions-Invocation\">Invocation</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Workbench_Actions-section-src-31524866_WorkbenchActions-GettheActivePerspectiveInformation\">Get the Active Perspective Information</a>    </p>\n</li></ul>    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-31524866_WorkbenchActions-Requirements\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Requirements</span></h2>\n    <p>The examples in this page use the <i class=\" \"><strong class=\" \">Prototype</strong></i> library, which is included by default inside a portal. However, the same concepts may be applied using other implementations.    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-31524866_WorkbenchActions-Invocation\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Invocation</span></h2>\n    <p>This command is executed immediately in a synchronous way.    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-31524866_WorkbenchActions-GettheActivePerspectiveInformation\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Get the Active Perspective Information</span></h2>\n    <p>To get information regarding the active perspective in the Studio, dispatch this command:    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\"> </code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">var activePerspective = dispatch($H({</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\tcontroller: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;portal.workbench&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">,</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\taction: </code><code class=\"string\">&quot;getActivePerspective&quot;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">}).toJSON());</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <p>The <i class=\" \">activePerspective</i> variable will hold a <i class=\" \">Map</i> that contains the following keys: <i class=\" \"><strong class=\" \">label, description</strong></i> and <i class=\" \"><strong class=\" \">id</strong></i>.    </p>\n    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=31524866\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Workbench Actions"});